answers.answer: Hi!Teeth braces while aligning the teeth can also cause a change in your facial looks. Ask your orthodontist if your facial look is due to this re-alignment. Since all other tests are normal, it is unlikely to be anything serious. Still, if in doubt, check for diabetes, thyroid disorder, anemia and worms in stool. Please consult your doctor regarding this. Take care!The medical advice given should not be considered a substitute for medical care provided by a doctor who can examine you. The advice may not be completely correct for you as the doctor cannot examine you and does not know your complete medical history. Hence this reply to your post should only be considered as a guiding line and you must consult your doctor at the earliest for your medical problem.

question: Hey!In the last past year I've noticed that the area under my cheekbones and my temporal fat pads have shrunken. Once other people have noticed something changing in my face, thinking I have lost weight even though I haven't, I went to the doctor.The only thing that has changed in the last past year was that I've started using Invisalign as part of my orthodontic teeth straitening.I have seen a few doctors, including a neurologist and her staff, and have done numerous blood checks, EMG, ect. and nothing came up unusual.My profile picture shows the before and after change (left - October 2012, right - August 2013).Do you have any idea what this symptom could be caused by?I appreciate your help!Tal.
title: Shrunken Cheeks And Temporal Fat Pads
